libptytty
------------------------------------------
Libptytty is a small library that offers pseudo-tty management in an
OS-independent way. It was created out of frustration over the many differences
of pty/tty handling in different operating systems for the use inside
rxvt-unicode.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.2.0-1
  libgcc1-11.2.0-1
  libptytty-devel-2.0+git20210804-1bl1
  libptytty0-2.0+git20210804-1bl1
  pkg-config-1.6.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.37-1
  cmake-3.20.0-1
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-11.2.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.2.0-1
  ninja-1.10.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/yusiwen/libptytty

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/yusiwen/libptytty.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libptytty-2.0+git20210804-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libptytty-2.0+git20210804-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libptytty-2.0+git20210804-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libptytty-2.0+git20210804-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libptytty0-2.0+git20210804-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libptytty-devel-2.0+git20210804-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libptytty)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libptytty.README
  /usr/share/doc/libptytty/CHANGES
  /usr/share/doc/libptytty/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libptytty/README

(libptytty0)
  /usr/bin/cygptytty-0.dll

(libptytty-devel)
  /usr/include/libptytty.h
  /usr/lib/libptytty.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libptytty.pc
  /usr/share/man/man3/libptytty.3.gz

